The paper deals with the problem of drawing non-planar graphs without crossings using partial edge drawings. This is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.DS, cs.GT). The paper also discusses the problem of computing the maximum total stub length in a given drawing, which is related to optimization (cs.DM) and algorithms (cs.SI).
